title: Difficult
text: In few words. It is an absolute Beauty from the outside, and a big disappointment from the inside. Other smaller churches in Palermo would be better to visit

title: Don't understand !
text:
I really don't understand why this museum has more than 3.5 stars! The interior is well designed and that's it! The Greek icons are modest. One can find better preserved ones in museums in Berlin, Rome and Madrid !
I was expecting more of THE ACROPOLIS museum!

title: Nice Falafel " with eggplants!"
text: I found the idea of putting eggplants in a falafel sandwich bizarre at first, but I have to admit I liked the taste of it. No other falafel place would do that in Syria or Lebanon. Worth a try

title: Overrated
text: I have to admit, I might had too high expectations. But the whole thing is just columns. To be honest the view of Athens and the sea you get from above is worth the money more than the Acropolis it self

title: Friendly staff good yogurt
text: We were advised by a worker called "Zol"! Very friendly and thorough. Yogurt was yummy and in different variation. I think it's a must to try in Athens. You can decide later if it's your thing or not

title: One of the best Momos
text: We tried three different types ! Meat is the best ! Actually one can only choose between 4 options. As desert you should try their cheese cake

title: Very impressive
text:
A must in Napoli !
Had the tour with Valentina. She was like the first tourist guide who was not irritated by tourists :). You will know what I mean after being in some touristy places there

title: Very good
text: Delicious food. People who think the waters are rude should spend more time in Napoli and get to know people

title: A Bit overrated . Not that much to see . Do not take a guide
text:
If ruins is what interest you, go to Ercolani !
Pompei is big and a lot of scenes just repeat themselves. Although our guide did a good Job, but an audio guide would be much better !

title: A must for archeological freaks. A LOT better than Pompei
text: First of all if you are staying only for a couple of days in Napoli, this is the place to go and not Pompei. It is much better reserved. An Audio Guide will be very helpful. An amazing look into history

title: One of the best in Sarajevo
text: Went there two times during my visit. Each time was no regret at all. The food was just delicious. Nice ambient as well

title: Overrated
text: The view from the windows were like the high point of the museum. We really expected more informations which were just not there. It is air conditioned, which is a big plus

title: Splendid K체nefe. Average Service
text: The k체nefe here is just good. The right fresh taste and the right amount of syrup, which is essential for the texture. The Tea as well is good here - in comparison to other Tea places we visited in Sarajevo -. The service could use some improvements.

title: Hipster and friendly
text: The inside decor is beautiful and the have OK sorts of Beers. Would not say it is a must in Sarajevo.

title: Essential
text: Probably the most photographed place in Sarajevo. Always a lot of people and nice atmosphere. The coppermakers shops are just there.

title: Delicious food, nice atmosphere
text: Very much liked the Kebabs ! As my girlfriend loves eggplants, We ordered Moussaka and Kawaj as well. so yummy !

title: The place for pies
text: Amazing for breakfast ! Delicious various pies to very acceptable prices ! Loved the Spinach and Anchovi and the siciliana pizza

title: Friendly and good Shisha
text: A very nice view to the sea ! Friendly staff, the shisha guy also. From 3 to 6 is their happy hour and one gets a free drink to the drink one orders

title: The best figs
text: This place had the best Gelato we had in our whole Rome - Florence journey ! The Fig taste was heavenly

title: Best Tiramisu
text: We tried the peanut and the classic Tiramisu. Both were very tasty ! Espresso is fine here as well. Highly recommend

title: Highly overrated
text: I would say it's a must during a rome visit, but a Blick from outside is really enough to get the idea of it

title: Unfriendly staff, salty food
text: The staff were very rude between each other and cared for a very unpleasant atmosphere! Food was average but both dishes we ordered were too salty !
place: Ristorante Pizzeria Forno a Legna 12 Apostoli

title: Good
text: We liked the food there, though fish could have been better ! Zucchini flower Dolma was a good choice as well as the tripe ala romana .

title: Friendly staff
text:
We stayed for two days in this Hotel. The staff was very friendly and helpful. Rooms small with functioning Air conditioning.
The area is good as well, although FULL of tourists ! The pool upstairs is not that deep or big and would fit only for relaxing not swimming
